{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc"},{"kind":"text","text":" = "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GSpawnChildSetupFunc","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GSpawnChildSetupFunc"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On POSIX platforms, the function is called in the child after GLib"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"has performed all the setup it plans to perform, but before calling"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"exec()"},{"type":"text","text":". Actions taken in this function will only affect the child,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not the parent."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"On Windows, the function is called in the parent. Its usefulness on"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Windows is thus questionable. In many cases executing the child setup"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"function in the parent can have ill effects, and you should be very"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"careful when porting software to Windows that uses child setup"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"functions."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"However, even on POSIX, you are extremely limited in what you can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"safely do from a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SpawnChildSetupFunc"},{"type":"text","text":", because any mutexes that were"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"held by other threads in the parent process at the time of the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fork()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"will still be locked in the child process, and they will never be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"unlocked (since the threads that held them don’t exist in the child)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"POSIX allows only async-signal-safe functions (see "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"signal(7)"},{"type":"text","text":") to be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"called in the child between "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"fork()"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"exec()"},{"type":"text","text":", which drastically limits"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the usefulness of child setup functions."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"In particular, it is not safe to call any function which may"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"call "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"malloc()"},{"type":"text","text":", which includes POSIX functions such as "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"setenv()"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"If you need to set up the child environment differently from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the parent, you should use "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_get_environ()"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_environ_setenv()"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_environ_unsetenv()"},{"type":"text","text":", and then pass the complete environment"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"list to the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn..."},{"type":"text","text":" function."}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/spawnchildsetupfunc"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SpawnChildSetupFunc","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Specifies the type of the setup function passed to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn_async()"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn_sync()"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn_async_with_pipes()"},{"type":"text","text":", which can, in very"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"limited ways, be used to affect the child’s execution."}],"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc"}],"title":"SpawnChildSetupFunc","roleHeading":"Type Alias","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"typealias","externalID":"s:4GLib19SpawnChildSetupFunca","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc"}]},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/SpawnChildSetupFunc":{"role":"symbol","title":"SpawnChildSetupFunc","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Specifies the type of the setup function passed to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn_async()"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn_sync()"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn_async_with_pipes()"},{"type":"text","text":", which can, in very"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"limited ways, be used to affect the child’s execution."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SpawnChildSetupFunc","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SpawnChildSetupFunc"}],"url":"\/documentation\/glib\/spawnchildsetupfunc"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"role":"collection","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/glib"}}}